olive oil
1 bunch asparagus
1 radish
1 apple
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet chicken thigh
1 tsp honey
½ packet Dijon mustard
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Trim ends of asparagus and halve.
• Thinly slice radish.
• Thinly slice apple into sticks.
• In a bowl, combine Nan's special seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken thigh, turning to coat. Season with salt and pepper.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook asparagus until tender, 5-6 minutes. Add a dash of water to pan to help asparagus cook. Transfer to a large bowl.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken thigh and cook, turning occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 14-16 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, add the honey and turn to coat.

TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink inside.

• Slice chicken.
• To the bowl with the asparagus, add mixed salad leaves, radish, apple, dijon mustard (see ingredients) and a drizzle of olive oil. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and season to taste.
• Divide asparagus salad between bowls. Top with spiced chicken. Enjoy!